In this article, President Biden addresses the press at FEMA and discusses the government's response to recent storms in Florida and South Carolina. He thanks the emergency personnel for their hard work and acknowledges the challenges posed by climate change. Biden calls on Congress to provide the necessary funds for disaster relief and emphasizes the importance of long-term recovery efforts. He also briefly mentions the drug epidemic and the need for border security measures to combat the influx of dangerous drugs. The President expresses hope that Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell will recover from his recent health issues and mentions his upcoming trip to Florida.